  "text": "How did you get rich? Have you ever heard of Home Depot? Yes. You've ever been in a Home Depot? Yes. That's how I got rich. What do you mean? That was my company. You were the founder of Home Depot? I was. How much is your company worth today? Probably 350 billion dollars. With a B? With a B. How old are you now? I'm 83 years old. At what age did you become a billionaire? That's a good question. I don't know. And you know what? It's good that I don't know. Because it was never about money to me. It was always about building values. The billionaire was only a byproduct of that. It was exactly right. Did you come from a lot of money growing up? No, I came from nothing. My dad was a pharmacist. He passed away at an early age. You didn't come from tremendous wealth. How did your upbringing shape the way that you think about money and risk? That's a great question. My upbringing was based on a set of values. My mother had an expression, you know, you do the right things for the right reasons and live with the consequences. At 36 years old, you were fired from your job. Right. Did you have people that doubted you or thought you were crazy when you started Home Depot? Absolutely. The first couple of years, people coming to our stores, you know, they say, these guys are nuts. They're crazy. Just ignore these guys. They're going to go broke. The volumes that we were doing were unbelievable. And that was all as a response of listening to what customers and the customer is always going to be right. The customer always comes first? The customer always comes first. I used to say at Home Depot, our ultimate sign of success is when our customers, they were so loyal, they would feel like they were disloyal or shopping someplace else. So you wanted your customers to become raving fans of your business? Absolutely. And I would say that to all of your listeners. You're 83 years old today. Right. If me and you died tomorrow and you had one more message to leave with the younger generation, what would that be? When you're talking about human relationships, you know, the reason I'm doing this interview is because I watched some of your other ones, which are great, but you develop a trust relationship with who you're talking to. You know, all these businesses, I think it's so critical that you develop trust, because once you have that trust level established, people will open up their hearts and their minds and eventually their wallets to you. Thank you so much for your time. Thank you. Do you have amazing advice to give back? Take care of yourself. I connect with all the millionaires and billionaires that interview. Could I get your contact? Yeah.",
